position
Interface Position<E>

Type Parameters:
E - The Position class represents a location into a list. A Position is defined relatively, that is, in terms of its neighbors. In a list, a position p will always be after a position q and before a position r(unless p is first or last position in the list). The Position interface provides only a method to extract element from the position.
All Known Subinterfaces:
BTPosition<E>, DecorablePosition<E>, Edge<E>, TreePosition<E>, Vertex<E>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AdjacencyListGraph.MyEdge, AdjacencyListGraph.MyVertex, ArrayPosition, BTNode, BTPos, DNode, MyPosition, TreeNode
public interface Position<E>
